name: Amazon River Piranhas
description:
Amazon River Piranha was named by the Tupi indigenous culture native to the Amazon, this freshwater fish “pirá” has fierce teeth “sainha” adopting the name of “pira nya”, literally meaning “bitting-fish”. It is one of those species that represent the diversity of a region with global strategic importance. 

Mind their teeth but be mindful of your footprint on biodiversity in your travels. 2309 × 1536 All rights reserved by the artist. July 2021.
